oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Tintype of Henry Jenks and unidentified individual
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Tintype of Henry Jenks and an unidentified individual. Jenks and a friend escaped (dug out) from Libby Prison in Richmond, Virginia, and made it safely back to Union territory to rejoin their regiments.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Fort Negley, Nashville, Davidson County, Tennessee
